narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: more advanced understanding of organic chemistry

Gained knowledge about NMR, IR, [4+2] cycloadditions, carboxylic acids, carboxylic acid derivatives, etc. associated with topics of the second half of organic chemistry. Established time management skills and organization.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Well organized with daily assignments as well as weekly alternating quizzes/exams.
I think this course could be improved with more practice problems and practice exams

One strength is the organization of the material. Every powerpoint, example, and problem set were very easy to locate and return to when reviewing for an exam. One weakness is the amount of material. It was difficult to recall all the examples from a particular topic and so the future, fewer examples might be more helpful so that students could spend more time on the most important reactions.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments:
Yes, if you need to take organic chemistry 2, the summer class is a great option.
It may be a little less thorough than in the semester.
I would recommend this course although I would also advise them that it requires a great deal of studying beyond the course materials

Yes. This course was very interesting and the applications of chemistry are found all over our daily lives. The material is well organized, but students should be prepared to prioritize studying the material for 5 weeks because the course is extremely demanding with the shortened semester.

narratives.question_text: The Canvas course site allowed me to identify and access required course materials easily.
How will you use the knowledge and skills you learned in this course in your future endeavors?
comments: The skills I have learned in this course have mainly helped me prepare for the MCAT and learn the chemistry concepts that are important not only for the pre-medical exam but also for my future career as a doctor.
Whether it be in conversations about medicine or daily life, the applications of chemistry are all around us and the knowledge I have gained from this course will be useful in a variety of aspects.
